post_text:
Panther Nation,

We want to thank our students, staff, and parents for a wonderful start to the 2020-2021 school year! The last two days have been great to see our Panthers and we are excited about the future. We welcomed 848 AGISD students, 400 PK-5th grade and 448 in Grades 6-12. Out of the 848 students, 86% attended in-person instruction and 14% were remote learners. We want to thank everyone for their patience, grace, and flexibility as we have gone through this first week. It is going to be a great school year. Go Panthers!

Dr. Cole McClendon, Superintendent

post_text:
Panther Praise-

Sometimes ‚Äúbehind-the-scenes‚Äù little changes go unnoticed but deserve recognition. Our AGISD Custodial Team deserves a huge ‚Äúshout-out.‚Äù In order to sanitize and deep clean our facilities every single day during the 2020-2021 school year, our custodians have split into a ‚Äúday‚Äù shift and NEW ‚Äúnight‚Äù shift. The night shift, without students and staff present, allows for very thorough disinfecting each night to prepare for the next day. I cannot express how appreciative I am of our custodial staff‚Äôs attitude in putting safety first. Five of ten custodians volunteered to work this new schedule, although I know it involved personal sacrifices on their part. Join me in thanking all of our custodians, maintenance employees that worked all summer in the heat, as well as cafeteria employees that prepared and helped deliver meals all Spring. We are blessed in AGISD with these dedicated people!

Panther Proud,
Dr. Cole McClendon
Superintendent

‚ÄúAGISD Meet the Teacher Day" will be Tuesday, August 11th, from 9am to 6pm. We are making this a day event in order to spread the foot-traffic and minimize hallway and classroom congestion. All visitors 10 years old and older are required to wear masks and have temperature screenings at campus checkpoints before entering the school. In the past we have welcomed all family members from parents, grandparents, uncles, aunts and cousins to our Meet the Teacher event; however, we ask that this year only guardians escort students into the buildings. Please feel free to bring your child's school supplies on this day and leave them in the classroom. Thank you for your patience, and we look forward to seeing you at AGISD Meet the Teacher Day 2020.

post_text: Another personnel change approved by our AGISD Board of Trustees on Monday night supports our COVID-19 response plan to be released soon. The board approved a second school nurse position specifically for secondary students. This is extremely proactive as it allows us to monitor/check symptoms for students on their home campus. This will avoid sending students across the district to one nurse clinic at elementary and reduce cross-contamination for any illness. We are pleased to announce Mrs. Jill Boykin has accepted the nurse position at our elementary campus. Applications are being accepted for our secondary nurse currently. Please contact Michael Mize, HS Principal, at mizem@agisd.org for details about applying. This is another great step in planning for the future and intentional strategy in preparing for the re-opening of schools! The comprehensive plan for re-opening AGISD, under current state and federal guidelines, will be released very soon.

post_text: Thanks to the AGISD Board of Trustees for ensuring we have a quality instructional program for Pre-Kindergarten. They have approved adding a third section of PK in order to keep class sizes small, comply with state guidelines, and better serve educational needs. All PK classes will be full-day for 2020-2021 and future years. We are seeking applicants for a PK teacher and aide for this new section. For more details about these vacancies and program guidelines, contact Mr. Kevin Wright, Elementary Principal, at wrightk@agisd.org

Eddie Caffey is a Senior at Alba-Golden High School. He has always loved to read. As a student Library Aide his senior year he gladly shared that love of reading with every student that entered the Library.

Eddie also enjoys being a proud member of the Alba-Golden Panther Band. He has been in band since his 6th grade year.

After graduation Eddie plans to attend Tyler Junior College to finish his Associate's Degree in Physics. Afterwards he plans to join the US Air Force and continue his education as he works towards a PhD in Astrophysics. His ultimate goal is to work for NASA, studying the universe.

This senior year will most definitely always be remembered by Mason and will be something that he will talk about for the rest of his life.

post_text:
Each day of the month of May, leading up to graduation, we would like to share two of our graduates with you. Today we begin with the Valedictorian of the A-G Class of 2020, Ann Marie Pendergrass.

Ann Marie has been accepted into the Honors College at Texas A&M Commerce where she plans to get her BS in Pre-Vet. She then plans to attend Texas A&M University and degree in Advanced Studies of Zoology & Veterinary Medicine. She has been awarded the Honors College Scholarship and Presidential Scholarship from TAMUC.

Ann Marie is also a student/athlete. She was the Volleyball Team Captain and was awarded 1st Team All-District and Academic All-District.
She has been a member of the National Honor Society for four years. Holding the title of NHS Secretary and Class Secretary. She was also voted the 2019/2020 Homecoming Queen by her peers.

Ann Marie is an outstanding and brilliant young lady who has a beautiful voice, but she is also free spirited and loved by many! We are SO proud of your accomplishments Ann Marie!! Your hard work is paying off!

The Alba-Golden Independent School District (ISD) Board of Trustees has employed Texas Association of School Boards (TASB) Executive Search Services to assist with the search for a new superintendent. The Board has requested that school personnel and the public be involved in developing a profile of the leadership qualities desired of the person the Board should seek to become the new superintendent.

If you have not already, we would encourage you to please fill out the following survey to give your input. Thank you for your participation!

post_text:
Most recent updates for our families:

As you know, Wood County has now issued a shelter in place. This is going to create some changes for us.

1. Beginning next week, the school building and facilities will be closed. This means that we will no longer be sending out paper packets from teachers. We encourage all parents to pick up packets from 1:00 - 8:00 pm THIS FRIDAY.

2. Meals will no longer be delivered every day. Instead, they will be delivered (by bus only) each Monday and Wednesday. Deliveries will begin at noon.

Though the buildings will be closed, school is still in session. We are all (school and home) doing our best to keep learning in progress. We thank you for the part that you are playing at home!!! As a way to help you, we have added a new link on our agisd.com website that is called Panther Connect. Panther Connect is the name we have chosen for our virtual school until this time passes. Please feel free to visit the "Panther Connect" link for valuable resources that our teachers are sharing with you. As always, be sure to contact us anytime!

In the day of social media where things spread like wildfire, and school posts are shared 97 times and viewed by 3500 in the matter of a few hours, it‚Äôs terrible to get your facts wrong! But... that‚Äôs what we‚Äôve done! We need to give a correction to the update that went out today: We are officially announcing closure through Friday, April 3rd, with school to resume on Monday, April 6th.

If the need arises to delay further, another three week period would be likely. All other facts are still accurate. We just got the ending date incorrect. Again, school closure is officially announced through Friday, April 3rd. We apologize for the error!

Alba Golden ISD will provide breakfast and lunch opportunities for all students starting March 17th and continuing Monday thru Friday until the district resumes onsite classes.

We will run regular bus route services to deliver the meals to individual students. The buses will leave the school at 10:00. There will be drive-thru services available at the school between 10:00 am and 12:00 pm for those that want to pick up here.

The meal will consist of a breakfast and lunch meal in one package. This is new territory for all of us and working together we can make this happen.

post_text:
I have been closely monitoring the Coronavirus (COVID- 19) and been in contact with local and state health authorities, the Commissioner of Education, and other school districts. At this time, due to concerns for the health and safety of our AGISD Family - students, staff, and community, Alba- Golden and the other Wood County schools will extend Spring Break one week.

This will allow us to further assess all student and staff travel. I understand this decision will directly impact everyone in our school community, and I thank you in advance for your patience and understanding.

Beginning Monday, March 16th, no extracurricular or UIL activities will take place until further notice. As decisions are made concerning the return to school the information will be made available as soon as possible. Updates will be posted on the school website.

School employees, please continue to monitor your email for further instructions.

Sincerely,

Eddie White
AGISD Interim Superintendent

post_text:
The Houston Livestock Show has been cancelled out of caution to prevent the spread of the CoronaVirus. AGISD students who were participating in the show had waited outside of the grounds all night before checking in yesterday morning. After they checked in, they discovered that the show was cancelled. Our agriculture staff who was with the students on site immediately reloaded the vehicles and started the return trip home yesterday afternoon, Wednesday, March 11, 2020.

At this time, there is no action to be taken by Alba-Golden ISD. If any further information comes forward or direction by state is obtained, I will update both the school website and the Facebook page. Please let me know if you have any questions by emailing me at whitee@agisd.org.

Sincerely,

Eddie White
Interim Superintendent, AGISD

Parents and Guardians,

Alba-Golden ISD administration would like to make you aware that the district received a report today of a potential threat to districts in the East Texas area. Upon receiving this report, an investigation immediately began. The district has determined that there were NO credible threats against Alba-Golden ISD.

Please be assured that we take every report seriously, and that the safety of students and staff members is the highest priority for Alba-Golden ISD.

STAAR Results will be available in the Student Portal for parents to look up on the following dates:

May 30th: April and May EOC-of-Course Exams

June 5th: STAAR Grades 5 & 8 Math & Reading Retest

June 12th: May STAAR Grades 3-8

Go to the Texas Assessment Management System (TAMS), which is available at www.texasassessment.com.
Click "Log In To Student Portal".
Click "Lookup Student Access Code." Enter your Student's LEGAL first name only, social security number (in the PEIMS ID box), and birthday and then click "Go" to get the Access Code.
The Access Code will pop up. Click "Go" again.
When you successfully login, you will see all of your student's test scores. You can click on any test to get a break down of how your student did in each area of the test, the number of questions they got correct, and the level of proficiency obtained.
You can obtain your student's Confidential Student Report (CSR) by clicking the "Download PDF's" button on the top right of the page.

These Lady Panthers claimed the title of Bi-District Champions with a score of 63-33 over Dallas Madison tonight. More information will be coming soon regarding details for their next matchup.

Meanwhile, you can catch boys basketball as they finish district play tomorrow night at home against Mineola. JV begins at 5:00, and Varsity will follow with senior night activities in between.

post_text:
School officials will be keeping an eye on inclement weather that may appear overnight, and any decision which needs to be made for a delay or school closure will be made by 6:00am in the morning.

You may find the latest updates at KLTV Channel 7, 99.9 KMOO, on this Alba-Golden ISD FB feed, or by signing up to receive notification from the Alba-Golden ISD app. The app is available for free download through the Apple App Store or through Google play.

post_text:
After a wild morning, things are settling in around A-G, and we are ready for a good day! Just a reminder that, in the case of unexpected events such as today, you may always look to this FB feed for the most recent updates. For your convenience, you may also download the Alba-Golden ISD school app from your iPhone or android App Store to receive updates on school happenings.

Thank you for being patient as it sometimes takes time to get back on track when unexpected issues arise.

post_text:
UPDATE - 8:54 AM: Power has been restored. School will begin at 10:00 am.

UPDATE - 6:45 AM: Currently, we are planning for a 10:00 start time. Buses will run on a two hour delay.

UPDATE - 6:20 AM: Maybe it was just an anticipated full-swing! Electricity is out at A-G. School officials are working on a plan for the day. Updates will be posted here ASAP!

AGISD will be back in full swing today! We are excited to see everyone return from a restful holiday season!

post_text:
Roughly 2,328 stuffed animals were donated to Tyler's Toyz tonight because of the generosity of our Alba-Golden family, those in our local and surrounding communities, the Mineola Yellowjackets, and Winona ISD. This compares to 643 items which were donated last year!

As far as the contest between the brothers goes, A-G came out pretty heavily on top; however, children in hospitals in the Northeast Texas area are the real winners! Thanks to each of you for your generous spirit! Merry Christmas and a very Happy New Year - from our family to yours!

post_text:
Just a reminder that tomorrow is the deadline to turn in all stuffed animals to be donated to Tyler's Toyz. You may drop off at AGISD, bring to the gym as your admission into the home basketball games tomorrow afternoon (boys play at 4:00, girls play after), or drop at any of the locally known drop boxes.

Thank you to all who chose to make a child's day brighter through your donation!
